│ Let me analyze the issue step by step.                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Understanding the Issue                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ The problem is that the transformation from the original code to using      │
│ `uadd.sat` is introducing more poison than the original code.               │
│                                                                             │
│ In the source:                                                              │
│ - `%notx = xor <2 x i32> %x, <i32 -1, i32 poison>` creates a vector where   │
│ the second element is poison                                                │
│ - `%a = add nuw <2 x i32> %yp, %notx` - the second element becomes poison   │
│ due to adding with poison                                                   │
│ - `%c = icmp ugt <2 x i32> %yp, %x` - comparison with poison in `%x`'s      │
│ second element makes the second element of `%c` poison                      │
│ - `%r = select <2 x i1> %c, <2 x i32> splat (i32 -1), <2 x i32> %a` - when  │
│ the condition is poison, the select returns the true value (splat -1)       │
│ according to LLVM's poison semantics for select                             │
│                                                                             │
│ In the target:                                                              │
